# REML v1.0 — Execution Mapping Layer

```text id="reml-001"
# ============================================
# EEE RUNTIME EXECUTION MAPPING LAYER
# REML v1.0
# ============================================

## PURPOSE

REML is responsible for transforming EEE system specifications (ESS) into executable runtime constructs.

It bridges:

• System Specifications (ESS)
→
• Execution Runtime (Agents + Events + Workflows)

--------------------------------------------------

## CORE PRINCIPLE

Nothing is executed directly from specification.

Everything must be compiled into an execution graph first.

--------------------------------------------------

## INPUT

REML accepts:

SYSTEM_SPEC (e.g. MIS v1.0)

AND transforms it into:

EXECUTION_RUNTIME_GRAPH
```

---

# 1. EXECUTION GRAPH MODEL

```text id="reml-graph"
EXECUTION_GRAPH {

nodes: [
    AGENTS,
    WORKFLOWS,
    EVENTS,
    APIs
],

edges: [
    agent_to_event,
    event_to_agent,
    workflow_to_agent,
    api_to_agent,
    event_to_workflow
]

}
```

---

# 2. AGENT RUNTIME BINDING

```text id="reml-agents"
AGENT EXECUTION BINDING:

AG-MEETING-COORD →
    triggers:
        MeetingStarted
        MeetingEnded

    executes:
        session_management

    emits:
        MeetingStarted
        MeetingEnded


AG-AI-ANALYST →
    listens:
        MeetingEnded

    executes:
        transcript_analysis
        decision_extraction

    emits:
        DecisionExtracted
        ActionItemCreated
```

---

# 3. EVENT DISPATCH ENGINE

```text id="reml-events"
EVENT DISPATCH RULES:

WHEN event occurs:

1. Identify event type
2. Match subscribed agents
3. Load agent context
4. Execute agent logic
5. Emit new events
6. Persist event log

RULE:
Events are immutable and replayable.
```

---

# 4. WORKFLOW EXECUTION ENGINE

```text id="reml-workflow"
WORKFLOW EXECUTION:

WF-MEETING-PROCESS:

STATE MACHINE:

CREATED
→ IN_PROGRESS
→ ENDED
→ ANALYZED
→ STRUCTURED

RULES:

- Each transition MUST be event-driven
- No direct state mutation
- All transitions logged as events
```

---

# 5. API EXECUTION BINDING

```text id="reml-api"
API → AGENT MAPPING:

POST /meetings/start →
    AG-MEETING-COORD

POST /meetings/end →
    AG-MEETING-COORD

RULE:
APIs never execute logic directly.
They only trigger agents.
```

---

# 6. RUNTIME FLOW (END-TO-END)

```text id="reml-flow"
FLOW:

1. User calls API
2. API triggers Agent
3. Agent emits Event
4. Event Dispatcher routes event
5. Target Agent executes
6. Workflow updates state
7. Events stored in Event Store
8. Observability layer records trace
```

---

# 7. EVENT STORE MODEL

```text id="reml-store"
EVENT STORE:

- Immutable log
- Fully ordered
- Replayable
- Correlated by ID

STRUCTURE:

Event {
    id
    type
    payload
    timestamp
    correlation_id
    source_agent
}
```

---

# 8. OBSERVABILITY MODEL

```text id="reml-observe"
OBSERVABILITY:

TRACK:

• Agent execution traces
• Event flows
• Workflow states
• API triggers

METRICS:

• Execution latency
• Event throughput
• Failure rates

LOGS:

• Structured only
• Correlated
• Immutable traces
```

---

# 9. FAILURE HANDLING ENGINE

```text id="reml-failure"
FAILURE MODEL:

IF agent fails:

→ retry (if allowed)
→ fallback agent (if defined)
→ escalate to orchestration layer

IF workflow fails:

→ trigger compensation events
→ rollback state via event replay
```

---

# 10. SYSTEM GUARANTEE MODEL

```text id="reml-guarantees"
GUARANTEES:

✔ Deterministic execution (given same events)
✔ Event replay capability
✔ No silent failures
✔ Full traceability
✔ No direct state mutation
```

